        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 23 at 8:12PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 810 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a severe thunderstorm 5
miles west of Timberon, moving east at 35 mph. This storm was
weakening as it pushed into the Sacramento Mountains, and is expecte
to be below severe limits as it moves east of Timberon. Another
strong thunderstorm was located near Pinehurst, west of Sacramento,
also moving east at about 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sacramento, Pinon, Weed, Hay Canyon, Avis, Miller Flats, Surveyors
Canyon, McDonald Flats, and Bluff Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
